verbose_text: Primary hyperparathyroidism is diagnosed by means of blood chemistry testing : raised PTH, hypercalcemia, hypophosphataemia, hyperuricaemia, anaemia, raised ESR, hypomagnesaemia, hypokalaemia, and hyperchloremic acidosis.
evidence: PTH, hypercalcemia, hypophosphataemia, hyperuricaemia, anaemia, raised ESR
